The paper discusses the use of formalism-based toolkits and notations for software development, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the use of specific notations such as Problem Frames, Requirements State Machine Language, and Event-B, which are related to programming languages (cs.PL) and systems and control (cs.SY). The focus on automotive applications suggests a connection to robotics (cs.RO) and embedded systems (cs.ET).
